<title>USA: Borland sees Q2 loss, cuts workforce 15 pct.</title>
<headline>Borland sees Q2 loss, cuts workforce 15 pct.</headline>
<dateline>SCOTTS VALLEY, Calif. 1996-10-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Borland International Inc said on Wednesday that it would cut 15 percent of its jobs on expectations of a second quarter loss of $0.32 to $0.36 per share.  </p>
<p>The company attributed the losses to the slow rate of its transition from desktop markets into corporate markets.</p>
<p>The company said the losses are expected on revenues of about $36 million for the second quarter, which it ended September 30.</p>
<p>Borland said it will cut 125 employees representing 15 percent of its workforce and realign its corporate structure worldwide to reduce costs.</p>
<p>The moves should save $15 million to $17 million a year and help the company return to profitability in fiscal 1998, said company Chief Executive Whitney Lynn.</p>
